WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.960 --> 00:00:03.839
DIGBY: I'm Digby Ernest Webster,

2
00:00:03.839 --> 00:00:05.280
I am an artist.

3
00:00:05.320 --> 00:00:07.000
(UPLIFTING GUITAR MUSIC)

4
00:00:09.599 --> 00:00:12.439
I will tell you something about Manu.

5
00:00:13.359 --> 00:00:16.679
I just like when he comes to hang out with me

6
00:00:16.679 --> 00:00:19.960
as a mate, he's a good person to know.

7
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.800
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

8
00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:26.719
I just love that painting I've just done.

9
00:00:26.719 --> 00:00:31.079
It's got Manu's kindness.

10
00:00:31.480 --> 00:00:35.119
Everything about him is a heart of gold.

11
00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:41.600
Manu, I just finished the portrait of the

12
00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:44.399
handsome man himself.

13
00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:47.759
So I did a portrait of a friend.

14
00:00:47.759 --> 00:00:49.320
His name's Neil,

15
00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:51.240
and he did a portrait of me too.

16
00:00:51.799 --> 00:00:53.719
And we got together,

17
00:00:53.719 --> 00:00:56.719
put my painting and his painting together as one,

18
00:00:56.719 --> 00:00:59.719
and entered it to the Archibald Prize.

19
00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:03.640
And they say...

20
00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:08.200
Your painting is in the room of 55 finalists!

21
00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:12.680
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

22
00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:18.200
I cannot believe I am up in this room with these guys,

23
00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:20.959
and they are very supportive.

24
00:01:21.480 --> 00:01:24.239
My partner, she came here,

25
00:01:24.239 --> 00:01:25.799
she saw this,

26
00:01:25.799 --> 00:01:30.159
and she voted for me in the People's Choice award.

27
00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:33.560
My work is a bit different in a way

28
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.359
because, you see, I've got a face,

29
00:01:36.359 --> 00:01:38.840
with a plain background on the back.

30
00:01:39.760 --> 00:01:43.000
I never do plain backgrounds, because I do it with crayons,

31
00:01:43.480 --> 00:01:47.879
I just do circling or lines with crayons.

32
00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:52.439
In paintings, it's really different,

33
00:01:52.439 --> 00:01:54.480
like, I just do this kind of background,

34
00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:59.040
and I put this figure in with his poncho.

35
00:02:01.319 --> 00:02:03.959
And he do the same thing with me over here,

36
00:02:03.959 --> 00:02:06.200
see, he's just mixing up colours,

37
00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:07.680
because he...

38
00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:10.039
This is his first time doing a portrait.

39
00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:13.960
He's known as a landscape artist.

40
00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:20.960
Right now, I am learning to do landscapes at the moment.

41
00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:25.000
I'm going in the other direction than him.

42
00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:29.080
Why I do art?

43
00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:35.159
Well, art is very a special thing to have in your body,

44
00:02:35.159 --> 00:02:37.120
to express.

45
00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:45.159
I just want to be a person who shows people with disability

46
00:02:45.159 --> 00:02:50.319
how they follow their footsteps, how they fulfil their dreams.

47
00:02:50.319 --> 00:02:55.800
By making movies, art, or dance....

48
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.080
or anything else...

49
00:02:58.319 --> 00:02:58.960
Just make it.
